+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Twk5gqsMUEL2qyhockWGn6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RUkHTnXQwowXervPjsA12T","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-circuit-debugger-design.md","content":"# Circuit Debugger Design\n\n## Overview\n\nBuild a circuit simulator and wire-swap debugger for logic gate circuits (AND, OR, XOR).\n\n## Components\n\n### `simulate(gates, inputs)`\n\nTopological simulation: iteratively process gates whose inputs are both resolved. No explicit topological sort needed — just iterate until all gates fire.\n\n### `findSwappedWires(gates)`\n\nStructural pattern matching against ripple-carry adder:\n\n1. **Bit 0 (half adder)**: `x00 XOR y00 -> z00`, `x00 AND y00 -> carry`\n2. **Bit N (full adder)**: 5 gates per bit:\n   - `xNN XOR yNN -> partial_sum`\n   - `partial_sum XOR carry_in -> zNN`\n   - `xNN AND yNN -> generate`\n   - `partial_sum AND carry_in -> propagate`\n   - `generate OR propagate -> carry_out`\n3. **Final bit**: last carry -> zNN+1\n\nFor each bit, trace the expected pattern. When a gate's output doesn't match expectations (wrong wire name, wrong gate type feeding into a role), identify the swapped pair. Collect all 8 swapped wires, return sorted.\n\n## Key Insight for Swap Detection\n\nBuild lookup maps (by input pairs and by output wire). For each bit position, determine what wires *should* be connected based on the adder pattern. When a mismatch is found, the wire that's in the wrong place and the wire that should be there form a swap pair.\n\n## File Structure\n\n- `src/index.ts` — Gate interface + both exported functions\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":439,"cache_read_input_tokens":24318,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":439},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inferen