e XOR gate at bit 3 has in1=\"c02\" (or whatever its input wire name is). Since c02 now comes from the AND(x03,y03) gate instead of the OR carry gate, that XOR gate is reading the wrong value.\n\nFor the algorithm: after tracing bit 2 with carry in = c01, it finds:\n- xorXY = XOR(x02, y02) -> partialSum (this was b02, after doSwap t02<->b02 it becomes t02)\n  \nWait, does doSwap fix inputs too or just outputs? Let me read the code.\n\nThe doSwap function in the code only swaps OUTPUT wire names, not inputs. This is correct because when gate outputs are swapped, the INPUT references in other gates DON'T change - they still reference the same wire NAMES. \n\nSo actually the algorithm needs to track that carry = a03 after bit 2 (because the OR gate at bit 2 outputs a03 after the swap), and then look for XOR(t03, a03) at bit 3. But the actual gate at bit 3 has inputs (t03, c02), not (t03, a03).\n\nThis means the algorithm CANNOT simply use the output name as carry. The carry is whatever wire the OR gate outputs, and downstream gates reference that wire by NAME. So the carry for bit 3 is whatever wire name the OR gate at bit 2 produces.\n\nAfter the c02<->a03 swap:\n- The OR gate at bit 2: originally had out=c02, after swap has out=a03\n- The XOR gate at bit 3: has inputs t03 and c02 (unchanged — inputs don't change)\n\nSo the XOR gate at bit 3 reads from wire c02, which now comes from the AND(x03,y03) gate (because that gate's output was swapped from a03 to c02). \n\nThe algorithm sets carry = a03 (OR gate output after swap), then looks for XOR(t03, a03). This gate doesn't exist — the XOR gate has inputs t03, c02. So the algorithm should detect that partialSum needs to be swapped.\n\nBut wait — there's also no XOR gate with a03 as input at all. The fallback code tries to find any XOR gate using carry as input. There's no XOR with a03 as input. So xorWithCarry = undefined and the algorithm continues with xorTC = undefined and skips this bit.\n\nTHAT's the bug. When carry